  • Classes 
    Class Description
    com.google.mu.util.stream.Cases
    Use findFirstElements() and/or findOnlyElements() methods together with Optional.or(java.util.function.Supplier<? extends java.util.Optional<? extends T>>) instead.
  • Methods 
    Method Description
    com.google.mu.util.BiOptional.both​(Optional<A>, Optional<B>)
    Use Optionals.both(java.util.Optional<? extends A>, java.util.Optional<? extends B>) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.Optionals.flatMapBoth​(Optional<A>, Optional<B>, CheckedBiFunction<? super A, ? super B, ? extends Optional<R>, E>)
    Use BiOptional.both(java.util.Optional<A>, java.util.Optional<B>) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.Optionals.mapBoth​(Optional<A>, Optional<B>, CheckedBiFunction<? super A, ? super B, ? extends R, E>)
    Use BiOptional.both(java.util.Optional<A>, java.util.Optional<B>) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.BiStream.consecutiveRunsFrom​(Stream<T>)
    Use biStream(stream).groupConsecutiveBy(identity(), counting()) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.BiStream.from​(Collection<T>, Function<? super T, ? extends K>, Function<? super T, ? extends V>)
    Use biStream(User::id, users) to create BiStream<UserId, User>, or, use biStream(users, User::getAccount) to create BiStream<User, Account>. Then use BiStream.mapKeys(java.util.function.BiFunction<? super K, ? super V, ? extends K2>) or BiStream.mapValues(java.util.function.BiFunction<? super K, ? super V, ? extends V2>) to apply further mappings.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.BiStream.grouping​(Function<? super T, ? extends BiStream<? extends K, ? extends V>>, Collector<? super V, ?, R>)
    Use MoreStreams.flatMapping(toKeyValues, BiCollectors.groupingBy(k -> k, reducer)).
    com.google.mu.util.stream.BiStream.mapIfPresent​(BiFunction<? super K, ? super V, ? extends Optional<? extends K2>>, BiFunction<? super K, ? super V, ? extends Optional<? extends V2>>)
    Use BiStream.mapIfPresent(BiFunction) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.BiStream.sorted​(Comparator<? super K>, Comparator<? super V>)
    Use BiStream.sorted(BiComparator) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.Cases.switching​(Collector<? super T, ?, ? extends Optional<? extends R>>...)
    Use Cases.cases(java.util.stream.Collector<? super T, ?, ? extends java.util.Optional<? extends R>>...) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.flatMapping​(Function<? super T, ? extends BiStream<? extends K, ? extends V>>, BiCollector<K, V, R>)
    Moved to MoreCollectors.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.flattening​(Function<? super T, ? extends Collection<? extends Map.Entry<? extends K, ? extends V>>>, BiCollector<K, V, R>)
    If you need to flatten a stream of Multimap, use something like flatMapping(m -> BiStream.from(m.asMap()), flatteningToImmutableSetMultimap()).
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.flatteningMaps​(BiCollector<K, V, R>)
    Moved to MoreCollectors.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.mapping​(Function<? super T, ? extends Both<? extends A, ? extends B>>, BiCollector<A, B, R>)
    Moved to MoreCollectors.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.toListAndThen​(Consumer<? super List<T>>)
    Moved to MoreCollectors.
    com.google.mu.util.stream.MoreStreams.uniqueKeys()
    Use maps.collect(flatteningMaps(toMap()) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.Substring.Pattern.delimit​(String)
    Use repeatedly().split(string) instead.
    com.google.mu.util.Substring.Pattern.iterateIn​(String)
